<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Fire Magic service</p>
    <h2>Why Fire Magic grills are the most repairable premium grill in California.</h2>

    <p>Fire Magic is RH Peterson Co's premium grill brand, manufactured in City of Industry, California since 1937. American-made, family-owned, no parent corporation. The Echelon Diamond series is what you find in the most premium outdoor kitchens across Beverly Hills, Newport Beach, Pacific Palisades, and Hidden Hills: high-BTU performance, hot surface ignition, the Magic Window in the hood, Diamond Sear cooking grids with lifetime warranty.</p>

    <p>Our techs service every Fire Magic grill currently in production and decades of legacy models. Echelon Diamond E660s, E790s, E1060s built-ins. Echelon Diamond stand-alones (portable). Aurora A660 and A790 (mid-premium). Choice multi-user. Plus the legacy Regal series (Regal 1, Regal 2), Custom 1, Custom 2, Monarch, and Elite Magnum.</p>

    <p>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura. Fire Magic ignition components and burner parts on the van. OEM only, sourced through RH Peterson's authorized distributor network.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS BY SERIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Series-aware diagnosis</p>
    <h2>The Fire Magic lineup, and what fails on each.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Fire Magic uses a clearer naming hierarchy than most premium grill brands. Echelon Diamond is the flagship; Aurora is mid-premium; Choice is entry premium; the Regal/Custom/Monarch/Elite legacy lines pre-date the 2014 platform reset. Diagnostics differ by line.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Echelon Diamond Series (current flagship, 2014 onwards)</h3>
    <p>The flagship line: E660s (30"), E790s (36"), E1060s (48"). All built-in or portable variants available, Diamond and Diamond Black aesthetic options. Hot surface ignition (110V) standard. Magic Window in the hood. Diamond Sear cooking grids included.</p>
    <p>Common failures by year:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Years 4 to 7:</strong> Hot surface igniter element burnout. Universal Fire Magic igniter OEM 3199-64 fits all Echelon E660/E790/E1060 plus Echelon side burners. Replacement is straightforward.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 5 to 8:</strong> Wire harness extension failure on built-in Echelon (OEM connects transformer pigtail to main harness). Replaced with current 24182-64 successor part.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 7 to 10:</strong> Backburner assembly (rotisserie zone). Different parts catalog for E790 (2012 and newer) versus E660 pre-2012. We stock both.</li>
      <li><strong>Years 8 to 12:</strong> Burner tube corrosion on coastal installs. Brass tubes typically last longer than stainless on coastal grills (counter-intuitive but true).</li>
      <li><strong>Years 10 plus:</strong> Master switch (digital LED system on Echelon Diamond) pits from current load over time.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Aurora Series (mid-premium, hot surface ignition since 2015)</h3>
    <p>A660 (30") and A790 (36"). Lower BTU output than Echelon, simpler control system, no Magic Window, no LED hood lights. Good build quality. Common failures: hot surface ignition same as Echelon, simpler wire harness, less expensive replacement parts overall.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Choice Multi-User</h3>
    <p>Entry premium for community and multi-residential applications. Built tough, simpler architecture. Failures concentrate at gas valves and ignition modules.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Legacy lines (pre-2014)</h3>
    <p>Regal 1, Regal 2, Custom 1, Custom 2, Monarch, Elite Magnum. Used different ignition technology: battery-powered spark modules and rotary spark igniters. We service these but parts availability varies. Some flavor grids and cooking grids are still available; ignition components may require upgrade kits to current architecture. Backburner electrode kits still in production (legacy single-rod design, OEM available).</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Searing Station and Power Burner accessories</h3>
    <p>Single and Double Searing Station: high-heat sear units that mount adjacent to main grill. Sear burner failure at 5 to 8 years is common (high-cycle thermal stress accelerates wear on these high-BTU units). Replacement straightforward; we use S21765Y sear flash tube on the Diamond-series sear lines and S21750Y main flash tube on standard Echelon zones.</p>
    <p>Diamond Power Burner: high-BTU dedicated burner unit. Different orifice catalog (NG vs LP). Failures: orifice clogging from cooking spillover, regulator drift.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TOP REPAIR SCENARIOS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Fire Magic repairs we see in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on Fire Magic service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Hot surface igniter failure (Echelon E660s/E790s/E1060s).</strong> Element burnt out. Universal OEM 3199-64 replacement. $180-280 part, 30-minute install.</li>
      <li><strong>Wire harness extension corrosion.</strong> Moisture intrusion at connector. Replacement 24182-64 successor. $120-180 part.</li>
      <li><strong>Master switch failure (Echelon Diamond LED system).</strong> Switch pits from continuous current draw. Replacement procedure documented in Fire Magic service manual; we follow it.</li>
      <li><strong>Burner replacement (any series).</strong> Cast stainless burner tubes pinhole at 8 to 12 years. Per-zone replacement.</li>
      <li><strong>Backburner assembly failure.</strong> Rotisserie zone igniter, electrode wire, or full backburner unit. Different parts for E790 (2012+) versus E660 (pre-2012).</li>
      <li><strong>Searing Station sear burner replacement.</strong> High thermal cycling causes sear burner failure at 5 to 8 years. Common repair on outdoor kitchens with Fire Magic searing stations.</li>
      <li><strong>Power Burner orifice cleaning/replacement.</strong> NG and LP orifices have different specs; we carry both.</li>
      <li><strong>Magic Window glass replacement.</strong> Distinctive Fire Magic hood feature. Replacement glass available for E1060, E790, E660, Aurora A660 and A790.</li>
      <li><strong>Power supply / transformer issues (built-in installs).</strong> Pre-2009 vs post-2009 transformer connectors are different. Identify vintage before ordering.</li>
      <li><strong>Cooking grid replacement.</strong> Diamond Sear stainless or Porcelain Cast Iron. Lifetime warranty on Diamond Sear (parts only, labor billable).</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
