    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five Fire Magic jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, Fire Magic Echelon Diamond E790s built-in (2018 install)</h3>
        <p>Owner called Wednesday, no spark on left main burner, others working. Tech tested hot surface igniter element on left zone: open circuit. Replaced with universal OEM 3199-64. Tested ignition cycle. Working. Total: $120 plus $215 part plus 30 minutes = $365.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pacific Palisades, Fire Magic Echelon E1060s portable (2015 install)</h3>
        <p>Multi-zone ignition issue. Diagnosed: master switch on Echelon Diamond LED panel had pitted from corrosion (coastal salt air at 9 years). Replaced master switch per Fire Magic service procedure. Tested all ignition zones, LED hood lights. Working. Total: $120 plus $310 part plus 1.5 hours = $610.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Newport Beach, Fire Magic Echelon E660s built-in (2019 install)</h3>
        <p>Backburner not lighting. Tested rotisserie burner: igniter electrode failed. Replaced single backburner electrode kit (E660 2012+ catalog). Total: $120 plus $135 part plus 45 min = $300.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Calabasas, Fire Magic Echelon Diamond E790s with Double Searing Station (2017 install)</h3>
        <p>Sear station not working, main grill fine. Both sear burners failed at 7 years (high thermal cycling on these high-BTU units is hard on burners). Replaced both sear burners simultaneously while the unit was apart. Total: $120 plus $580 (2 sear burners) plus 1.5 hours = $850.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bel Air, Fire Magic Aurora A660 built-in (2016 install)</h3>
        <p>Won't ignite at all. Diagnosed: wire harness extension corroded at the transformer connection. Replaced 24182-64 successor harness. Tested ignition. Working. Total: $120 plus $145 part plus 45 min = $310. Customer's previous shop had quoted "needs new transformer plus new wire harness, $850."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for Fire Magic, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>All current Fire Magic Echelon Diamond series (E660s, E790s, E1060s plus black diamond variants, built-in and portable)</li>
      <li>Aurora A660 and A790</li>
      <li>Choice multi-user</li>
      <li>Legacy: Regal 1, Regal 2, Custom 1, Custom 2, Monarch, Elite Magnum</li>
      <li>Echelon Diamond Power Burner</li>
      <li>Single and Double Searing Station</li>
      <li>Echelon Diamond side burners</li>
      <li>Echelon Diamond griddles (built-in and portable)</li>
      <li>Diamond Digital Thermometer system</li>
      <li>Echelon Pizza Oven (gas-fired only)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new Fire Magic grill installation (warranty installs go through authorized RH Peterson dealer network); custom Fire Magic cabinetry modification (metal fabricator trade); wood-fired pizza oven inserts (we do gas-fired only).</p>

    <p>If your grill is under Fire Magic warranty (most Echelon components carry 1-year, 5-year, or lifetime warranties depending on the part: burners and stainless are typically lifetime), we recommend going through Fire Magic's authorized dealer network first. We're happy to assess and tell you if the failure is warranty-eligible.</p>
  </div>
</section>

